   "source": [
    "### Import barrier condition"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "de77c5e0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "MetaChat provides a function `mc.pp.load_barrier_segments` to import this barrier information. The coordinate order in Napari may differ from that in Visium; you can define the order using `coord_cols`. The adata uses `tissue_hires_scalef` coordinates during import, while the images use `tissue_lowres_scalef`. Since we directly annotate barriers on the images, we should adjust the `scale` to align with the adata data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "d93d9df9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dict_scale = adata.uns['spatial']['Visium_HD_Mouse_Small_Intestine_lowres_image']['scalefactors']\n",
    "scale = dict_scale['tissue_hires_scalef']/dict_scale['tissue_lowres_scalef']\n",
    "barrier_segs = mc.pp.load_barrier_segments(\"datasets/mouse_small_intestine/barrier.csv\", coord_cols=(\"axis-2\", \"axis-1\"), scale=scale)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b47609de",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can use simple visualization to check whether the barrier coordinates are correct."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "c2b5fb8f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 500x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Check barriers\n",
    "clusters = adata.obs[\"Cluster\"] if \"Cluster\" in adata.obs else None\n",
    "XY = np.asarray(adata.obsm[\"spatial\"], float)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,5))\n",
    "cats = pd.Categorical(clusters)\n",
    "ax.scatter(XY[:,0], XY[:,1], s=8, c=cats.codes, cmap=\"tab20\", edgecolor=\"none\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for (a, b) in barrier_segs:\n",
    "    x = [a[0], b[0]]\n",
    "    y = [a[1], b[1]]\n",
    "    ax.plot(x, y, lw=2, c=\"black\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_aspect(\"equal\", adjustable=\"box\")\n",
    "ax.invert_yaxis()\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Clusters with barrier segments\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4d1d48e3",

    "\n",
    "ax.set_box_aspect(1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b5692a8f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Compute cost distance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c29ad32e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Determined dis_thr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a06d1e5b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After identifying the LRCs, we compute the cost between any pair of points. In general, the cost is determined by the Euclidean distance; however, when LRCs and anatomical barriers are considered, the cost is redefined based on these additional constraints."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "90f986bf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The parameter `dis_thr` is critical for defining how far a metabolite signal is assumed to propagate. Since the spatial scale of coordinates varies across datasets, it is important to visually inspect and adjust `dis_thr`. The function `mc.pl.plot_dis_thr` allows users to visualize this threshold by specifying the distance (`dis_thr`) and the central spot (spot_index), enabling intuitive calibration of the propagation range. Here we use `dis_thr=80`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "ab788001",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Axes: title={'center': 'Spots within dis_thr=80 of spot 1000'}, xlabel='spatial1', ylabel='spatial2'>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 19,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dis_thr = 80\n",
    "mc.pl.plot_dis_thr(adata = adata, dis_thr = 80, spot_index = 1000)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ff63df8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The function mc.pp.compute_costDistance() calculates the spatial cost distance matrix between all spots, integrating both Euclidean proximity and long-range channel (LRC) effects. Specifically, it adjusts the pairwise distances according to the defined `LRC_type` and their corresponding `LRC_strength`, allowing metabolite diffusion or communication along designated LRC paths to be modeled more realistically. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b2118a49",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The parameters `LRC_type` and `LRC_source` should correspond to the names used in adata.obs['LRC_<LRC_type>_<LRC_source>_filtered'].\n",
    "A higher value of `LRC_strength` indicates a stronger influence of long-range communication, effectively expanding the propagation range through LRCs. The parameter `dis_thr` should match the distance threshold defined in the previous step.\n",
    "We support and recommend setting `use_parallel = True` and increasing `n_jobs` within the limits of your system performance, as this can significantly accelerate the computation of the cost distance matrix. The resulting distance matrix is stored in adata.obsp (e.g., adata.obsp['spatial_distance_LRC_Blood']) and can be used in downstream analyses of metabolic cell communication."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "36ed7f00",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Computing baseline spatial distance without LRC.\n",
      "  Barrier condition is considered\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "  Building visible graph with paralleling 64 CPU cores...: 100%|██████████| 5325216/5325216 [00:11<00:00, 476976.14it/s]\n",
      "  Computing shortest paths for non-visible points: 100%|██████████| 3952490/3952490 [05:29<00:00, 12004.83it/s]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Computing spatial distance with LRCs.\n",
      "  Processing LRC type: Blood\n",
      "    Constructing graph for each LRC subcluster.\n",
      "    Computing shortest path between two points in Blood.\n",
      "      For the cluster 1 in Blood.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "100%|██████████| 1259/1259 [00:23<00:00, 54.01it/s]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "    Incorporating LRC strength of 'Blood' into cost distance matrix (strength = 5).\n",
      "adata.obsp['spatial_distance_LRC_Blood'] has been saved.\n",
      "Finished!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mc.pp.compute_costDistance(\n",
    "    adata = adata,\n",
    "    LRC_type = ['Blood'],\n",
    "    LRC_strength = [5],\n",
    "    LRC_source = \"marker\",\n",
    "    dis_thr = dis_thr,\n",
    "    k_neighb = 5,\n",
    "    barrier = True,\n",
    "    barrier_segments = barrier_segs, # consider barrier condition.\n",
    "    use_parallel = True,\n",
    "    n_jobs = 64\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "ef8dec21",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
